The new D&D game booklet I made for this semester’s Summercell campaign. 
This time around, i improved on the booklet as a quickstart guide that basically condenses the essentials of the Player’s Handbook into a simple chapbook.
Features rules on movement, actions, ability checks, dice rolls, how to create a character, breakdowns on race and class, a modified character sheet, story introduction, example spells and abilities for each class, common use armor and weapons, magical weapons, home brew Evislan weapons, and general terms as well as a few pieces of artwork that I created for the booklet and campaign itself.

:
:
:
#dnd #illustration #dungeonsanddragons #fantasy #fantasyart #dndhomebrew .

Some DnD weapons cards that I made for the current campaign. In the story, the players are prisoners being held in a facility where they’re forced to take part in gladiatorial combat. Since the players are prisoners, they are never actively armed unless they have visited the armory for when we have a session inside the gladiator arena. In order to keep track of weapons that don’t “belong” to the character, I created these cards. They also give players the option to choose a completely different weapon each time the prisoners are sent out to the arena. 
I drew and inked each weapon arrangement as an uncut card sheet, photocopied the pages onto orange card stock, cut out all the cards, and then gave them all an individual laminate layer. 
So far, they seem to be working well.
